Feature: Set parent and description during branch creation (checkout -b)
  Command: pgit checkout -b <branch name> <-p parent-name> <-d description>
  Parameters along with flags given in <> are optional. Whatever left empty will be asked as an input in TUI form
  When user gives this, if all 3 (branch name, parent name and description) are given, no TUI will open. We can just show a
  message saying new branch has been created with below info:
  Branch: branch-name
  Parent: parent
  Desc: description

  When atleast 1 of them is missing, the command will open inline TUI where then can enter each of these fields. branch name and
   description are text fields. Parent should give parent picker (Tree branch structure with description column alone). It can
  open in a pane below or pane to the right. I recommend trying both variants, then based on my opinion, retain one. Control it
  with flags for now

  As usual, check if any of the components present in https://github.com/charmbracelet/bubbletea?tab=readme-ov-file or
  https://github.com/charmbracelet/huh or https://github.com/charmbracelet/lipgloss is useful
